I tried to put a name to a face as early as I could to make it easier to think of them as important rather than a background character. I made sure to keep a running timeline in my head and connect the characters across scene changes. I would find it acceptable to give only the gist of what happened. For example, "The guards stopped him in the hall. He rolled over and said take me home". I would not expect a person to have the mental capacity to reliably comprehend too many details in their lucid state.
